snippet.textDisplay:
'They've played the same as Manchester City, and they are 17 points... no 15 points clear of Manchester City.' No, I think you'll find that Liverpool are 17 points clear of Manchester City. 61 - 44 = 17. So Liverpool have to lose 5 and draw 1, and Manchester City have to win 6 comparatively, just for Manchester City to be on equal points. Because of Liverpool defeating Tottenham, now Liverpool have over double the amount of points that they do. I hope Tottenham are able to bounce back this season, what happened to them comparative to their achievements last season. I'm a Liverpool supporter, but I'd like to see Tottenham do well, their players are too good for Tottenham to be 8th in the Premier League.

Saying that, I don't think Liverpool were lucky against Tottenham. Tottenham had opportunities to score, yes, but so did Liverpool. Liverpool just managed to capitalize on one of the chances that they forged. Liverpool played from the back and controlled the game, building from the back to create their chances. Tottenham sat back with a line of 5 in defence, and the keeper. They wanted to catch Liverpool on the counter attack, some of the time with long balls. Tottenham were under so much pressure from Liverpool's high-pressing at times, that they hoofed the ball up-field from just outside their 18 yard box, and/or kicked it in to touch just to get rid of the ball. Sometimes, they even played it up field, and there were no Tottenham players even in that half of the pitch, they were just so desperate to get the ball away fromt their goal.

Liverpool deserved the win, but I would have liked to see Tottenham get a goal at least, their performance deserved that.
